---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
const updated = '15 March 2024';
---

<MainLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Neovantis"
  description="Neovantis Privacy Policy — how we collect, use, and protect your personal information in compliance with the Protection of Personal Information Act (POPIA)."
>

  <section class="page-hero" style="min-height:35vh;">
    <div class="page-hero-bg" style="background-image:url('https://picsum.photos/id/1/1920/600');filter:brightness(0.2) saturate(0.4);"></div>
    <div class="page-hero-overlay"></div>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-hero-content">
        <h1 style="font-size:clamp(2rem,4vw,3.5rem);">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <div class="accent-bar" style="margin-left:auto;"></div>
        <p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55);font-size:0.85rem;margin-top:0.75rem;">Last updated: {updated}</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--lg">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="prose">

        <div class="alert">
          This Privacy Policy is governed by the <strong>Protection of Personal Information Act 4 of 2013 (POPIA)</strong>. By using this website, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this policy.
        </div>

        <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
        <p>Neovantis (Pty) Ltd ("Neovantis", "we", "our", "us") is a South African medical technology company based in Durban, KwaZulu-Natal. We are the responsible party for personal information collected through this website in terms of POPIA.</p>
        <p><strong>Contact:</strong> info@neovantis.co.za | 031 463 1188</p>

        <h2>2. What Personal Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>We collect personal information that you voluntarily provide to us through our website forms, including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Full name</li>
          <li>Professional title and practice / organisation name</li>
          <li>Email address and telephone number</li>
          <li>Enquiry content and product interests</li>
          <li>Geographic location (province / region)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We also collect standard technical data through your use of this website, including IP address, browser type, pages visited, and session duration, via our hosting and analytics infrastructure.</p>

        <h2>3. Why We Collect Your Information</h2>
        <p>We collect and process your personal information for the following purposes:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>To respond to enquiries submitted through our contact and distributor forms</li>
          <li>To provide product information, quotations, and clinical documentation</li>
          <li>To process and manage distribution partnership applications</li>
          <li>To send relevant product and company updates where you have opted in</li>
          <li>To improve the performance and content of our website</li>
          <li>To comply with legal and regulatory obligations</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
        <p>We process your personal information on the following grounds under POPIA:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Consent:</strong> Where you have provided explicit consent by submitting a form or opting in to communications</li>
          <li><strong>Contractual necessity:</strong> Where processing is required to fulfil a request or enquiry you have initiated</li>
          <li><strong>Legitimate interest:</strong> Where processing is necessary for our legitimate business interests and these are not overridden by your rights</li>
          <li><strong>Legal obligation:</strong> Where processing is required to comply with applicable law</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. How We Store and Protect Your Information</h2>
        <p>Your personal information is stored on secure servers managed by our website hosting provider (Netlify) and our business communication systems. We implement appropriate technical and organisational measures to protect your personal information against unauthorised access, disclosure, alteration, and destruction.</p>
        <p>We do not store payment card information on our systems.</p>

        <h2>6. Sharing of Personal Information</h2>
        <p>We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information to third parties. We may share your information with:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Our website and email service providers, to the extent necessary to deliver our services</li>
          <li>Legal and regulatory authorities, where required by law</li>
          <li>Professional advisors (legal, financial) under confidentiality obligations</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. Retention of Personal Information</h2>
        <p>We retain personal information only for as long as is necessary to fulfil the purposes for which it was collected, or as required by law. Enquiry records are typically retained for 5 years for business continuity purposes. You may request deletion of your information at any time (see Section 9).</p>

        <h2>8. Cookies and Website Analytics</h2>
        <p>This website may use standard analytics tools to measure traffic and improve user experience. These tools may set cookies — small text files stored on your device. You may disable cookies through your browser settings; however, this may affect the functionality of certain website features.</p>

        <h2>9. Your Rights Under POPIA</h2>
        <p>As a data subject, you have the following rights under POPIA:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Right of access:</strong> To request confirmation of whether we hold your personal information and to receive a copy</li>
          <li><strong>Right to correction:</strong> To request correction of inaccurate or incomplete personal information</li>
          <li><strong>Right to erasure:</strong> To request deletion of your personal information, subject to legal retention requirements</li>
          <li><strong>Right to object:</strong> To object to the processing of your personal information for direct marketing purposes</li>
          <li><strong>Right to complain:</strong> To lodge a complaint with the Information Regulator of South Africa</li>
        </ul>
        <p>To exercise any of these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:info@neovantis.co.za" style="color:var(--blue-accent);">info@neovantis.co.za</a>.</p>

        <h2>10. Information Regulator</h2>
        <p>If you are unsatisfied with our response to a privacy concern, you may contact the Information Regulator of South Africa:</p>
        <p>Website: <a href="https://inforegulator.org.za" style="color:var(--blue-accent);" target="_blank" rel="noopener">inforegulator.org.za</a><br/>
        Email: inforeg@justice.gov.za</p>

        <h2>11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Material changes will be communicated via a notice on this website. Continued use of this website after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.</p>

      </div>

      <div style="margin-top:3rem;padding-top:2rem;border-top:1px solid var(--border);">
        <a href="/" class="btn btn-ghost">← Back to Home</a>
        <a href="/terms" class="btn btn-ghost" style="margin-left:1rem;">Terms of Use</a>
        <a href="/medical-disclaimer" class="btn btn-ghost" style="margin-left:1rem;">Medical Disclaimer</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</MainLayout>
